{"parse":{"title":"Holy Spirit in Christian art","pageid":31305637,"revid":823397474,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg/220px-Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"340\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg/330px-Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg/440px-Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"876\" data-file-height=\"1353\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Holy Spirit as a dove in the <a href=\"/wiki/Annunciation\" title=\"Annunciation\">Annunciation</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Rubens\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Rubens\">Rubens</a>, 1628</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b><a href=\"/wiki/Holy_Spirit_(Christianity)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Holy Spirit (Christianity)\">Holy Spirit</a></b> has been represented in <b><a href=\"/wiki/Christian_art\" title=\"Christian art\">Christian art</a></b> both in the <a href=\"/wiki/Eastern_Church\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Eastern Church\">Eastern</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Western_Church\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Western Church\">Western Churches</a> using a variety of depictions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Earls70_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Earls70-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Gardner349_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Gardner349-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Lossky_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Lossky-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The depictions have ranged from nearly identical figures that represent the three persons of the <a href=\"/wiki/Holy_Trinity\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Holy Trinity\">Holy Trinity</a> from a dove to a flame.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Eugene121_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Eugene121-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Holy Spirit is often depicted as a <a href=\"/wiki/Dove\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dove\">dove</a>, based on the account of the Holy Spirit descending like a dove on <a href=\"/wiki/Baptism_of_Jesus\" title=\"Baptism of Jesus\">Jesus at his baptism</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Joel14_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Joel14-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> In many paintings of the <a href=\"/wiki/Annunciation\" title=\"Annunciation\">Annunciation</a>, the Holy Spirit is shown in the form of a dove, coming down towards Mary on beams of light, as the <a href=\"/wiki/Gabriel\" title=\"Gabriel\">Archangel Gabriel</a> announces <a href=\"/wiki/Christ\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Christ\">Christ</a>'s coming to <a href=\"/wiki/Mary,_the_mother_of_Jesus\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mary, the mother of Jesus\">Mary</a>.\n</p><p>A dove may also be seen at the ear of <a href=\"/wiki/Saint_Gregory_the_Great\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Saint Gregory the Great\">Saint Gregory the Great</a>\u2500as recorded by his secretary or other church father authors, dictating their works to them.\n</p><p>The dove also parallels the one that brought the olive branch to <a href=\"/wiki/Noah\" title=\"Noah\">Noah</a> after the deluge, as a symbol of peace.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Joel14_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Joel14-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The book of Acts describes the Holy Spirit descending on the <a href=\"/wiki/Twelve_apostles\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Twelve apostles\">apostles</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/Pentecost\" title=\"Pentecost\">Pentecost</a> in the form of a wind and tongues of fire resting over the apostles' heads. Based on the imagery in that account, the Holy Spirit is sometimes symbolized by a flame.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Eugene121_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Eugene121-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>There are also depictions of the Holy Spirit in the <a href=\"/wiki/Book_of_Genesis\" title=\"Book of Genesis\">book of Genesis</a>. In The <a href=\"/wiki/Vatican_Museums\" title=\"Vatican Museums\">Vatican</a> Museum in Rome is a carved stone sarcophagus depicting the Holy Trinity as three bearded men during the creation of <a href=\"/wiki/Eve\" title=\"Eve\">Eve</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Robert68_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Robert68-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The majority of early Christian art depicts The Holy Spirit in an anthropomorphic form as a human with two other Identical human figures representing <a href=\"/wiki/God_the_Father\" title=\"God the Father\">God the Father</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Jesus_Christ\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jesus Christ\">Jesus Christ</a>. They either sit or they stand grouped closely together. This is used to portray the unity of The Godhead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Jane546_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Jane546-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Andrei54_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Andrei54-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Holy Spirit is represented in various artistic mediums such as stained glass windows and calligraphy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Lois126_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Lois126-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Gallery\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Gallery</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#In_the_Trinity\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">In the Trinity</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Pentecost\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Pentecost</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Gallery\">Gallery</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Holy_Spirit_in_Christian_art&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Gallery\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg/88px-Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg\" width=\"88\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg/132px-Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg/176px-Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2328\" data-file-height=\"3168\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Baptism_of_Jesus\" title=\"Baptism of Jesus\">Baptism of Christ</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Pietro_Perugino\" title=\"Pietro Perugino\">Pietro Perugino</a>, circa 1498\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg/109px-Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg\" width=\"109\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg/163px-Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg/217px-Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2024\" data-file-height=\"2235\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Scene by <a href=\"/wiki/Filippo_Lippi\" title=\"Filippo Lippi\">Filippo Lippi</a>, 1459\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Andrea_del_Verrocchio,_Leonardo_da_Vinci_-_Baptism_of_Christ_-_Uffizi.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Andrea_del_Verrocchio%2C_Leonardo_da_Vinci_-_Baptism_of_Christ_-_Uffizi.jpg/101px-Andrea_del_Verrocchio%2C_Leonardo_da_Vinci_-_Baptism_of_Christ_-_Uffizi.jpg\" width=\"101\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Andrea_del_Verrocchio%2C_Leonardo_da_Vinci_-_Baptism_of_Christ_-_Uffizi.jpg/151px-Andrea_del_Verrocchio%2C_Leonardo_da_Vinci_-_Baptism_of_Christ_-_Uffizi.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Andrea_del_Verrocchio%2C_Leonardo_da_Vinci_-_Baptism_of_Christ_-_Uffizi.jpg/201px-Andrea_del_Verrocchio%2C_Leonardo_da_Vinci_-_Baptism_of_Christ_-_Uffizi.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1565\" data-file-height=\"1864\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Both <i><a href=\"/wiki/Hand_of_God_(art)\" title=\"Hand of God (art)\">Hands of God</a></i> (relatively unusual) and the Holy Spirit as a dove in <a href=\"/wiki/The_Baptism_of_Christ_(Verrocchio)\" title=\"The Baptism of Christ (Verrocchio)\">Baptism of Christ, by Verrocchio</a>, 1472.\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:17px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cd/Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg/120px-Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"116\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cd/Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg/180px-Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cd/Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg/240px-Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1977\" data-file-height=\"1908\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Stained glass window, <a href=\"/wiki/Zabrze\" title=\"Zabrze\">Zabrze</a>, Poland\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"In_the_Trinity\">In the Trinity</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Holy_Spirit_in_Christian_art&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: In the Trinity\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Angelsatmamre-trinity-rublev-1410.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0b/Angelsatmamre-trinity-rublev-1410.jpg/96px-Angelsatmamre-trinity-rublev-1410.jpg\" width=\"96\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0b/Angelsatmamre-trinity-rublev-1410.jpg/144px-Angelsatmamre-trinity-rublev-1410.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0b/Angelsatmamre-trinity-rublev-1410.jpg/193px-Angelsatmamre-trinity-rublev-1410.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1300\" data-file-height=\"1619\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Andrei_Rublev\" title=\"Andrei Rublev\">Andrei Rublev</a>'s Trinity, representing the Father, Son and Holy Spirit in a similar manner.\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:La_Trinit%C3%A9_et_tous_les_saints.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/La_Trinit%C3%A9_et_tous_les_saints.jpg/79px-La_Trinit%C3%A9_et_tous_les_saints.jpg\" width=\"79\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/La_Trinit%C3%A9_et_tous_les_saints.jpg/118px-La_Trinit%C3%A9_et_tous_les_saints.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/La_Trinit%C3%A9_et_tous_les_saints.jpg/158px-La_Trinit%C3%A9_et_tous_les_saints.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"736\" data-file-height=\"1119\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Trinity and all the saints, Jean Fouquet, 15th century\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:BLRoyal2BXVFol010vTrinity.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/BLRoyal2BXVFol010vTrinity.jpg/81px-BLRoyal2BXVFol010vTrinity.jpg\" width=\"81\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/BLRoyal2BXVFol010vTrinity.jpg/122px-BLRoyal2BXVFol010vTrinity.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/BLRoyal2BXVFol010vTrinity.jpg/163px-BLRoyal2BXVFol010vTrinity.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"439\" data-file-height=\"646\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Multiple head representation, 16th century\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Trinity_tikhon_filatiev.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Trinity_tikhon_filatiev.jpg/102px-Trinity_tikhon_filatiev.jpg\" width=\"102\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Trinity_tikhon_filatiev.jpg/153px-Trinity_tikhon_filatiev.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Trinity_tikhon_filatiev.jpg/204px-Trinity_tikhon_filatiev.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"454\" data-file-height=\"535\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Russian icon of <a href=\"/wiki/Holy_Trinity\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Holy Trinity\">Holy Trinity</a>\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:38.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Romanesque_tympanum_-_Abbaye_aux-dames_Sainte-Trinite_Caen.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Romanesque_tympanum_-_Abbaye_aux-dames_Sainte-Trinite_Caen.jpg/120px-Romanesque_tymp